The paper deals with adversarial attacks on neural models, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on probabilistic autoregressive forecasting models, which are used in time series analysis, and hence the paper could also be classified under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the use of Monte-Carlo estimation, which is a technique used in computational statistics (cs.ST) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to two specific tasks - stock market trading and prediction of electricity consumption - which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
